## SEVENTH ADHYÂYA <span id="fr_616"></span>[2](#fn_614.md).

### FIRST KHA*ND*A.

1\. My speech rests in the mind, my mind rests in speech <span
id="fr_617"></span>[3](#fn_615). Appear to me (thou, the Highest Self.md)!
You (speech and mind) are the two pins <span
id="fr_618"></span>[4](#fn_616) (that hold the wheels.md) of the Veda. May
what I have learnt not forsake me <span id="fr_619"></span>[5](#fn_617.md).
I join day and night with what I have learnt <span
id="fr_620"></span>[6](#fn_618.md). I shall speak of the real, I shall
speak the true. May this protect me, may this protect the teacher! May
it protect me, may it protect the teacher, yea, the teacher!

